cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper proposes a new decision tree extension that focuses on interpretability and compression while maintaining good performance. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that cs.LG and cs.AI are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impurity calculation and pure ending condition, which are fundamental concepts in data mining, indicating that cs.DM is another possible sub-category. Additionally, the proposed method involves soft labels and cross-validation, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
